  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Meta-tool runs in-proc within the BFF Chat agent.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter auth applies at calling endpoint (`/api/chat/`). Caller authorization checked inside the meta-tool before returning detail; Tool the caller lacks permission to invoke returns an error (not the detail).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. Dataverse client + JsonSerializerOptions injected via `[FromServices]`. No service-locator.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts boundary. `GetResourceDetail` is NOT exposed via the facade — internal SK function only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit Tier 2 + Tier 3 applies automatically via middleware. No manual audit calls.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors propagate to the calling endpoint as ProblemDetails. Internal exceptions wrapped with resource-id context.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Use existing Dataverse client + JSON. Zero new NuGet packages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge: placement (in BFF, latency-coupled to Chat agent). Zero publish-size delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">spec.md FR-11: returns full schema + SourceHints per parameter (which can be auto-resolved from surface context vs which require user input).</constraint>
  </constraints>

