  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; task 020 merged or branch-loadable; Dataverse client available in BFF DI.</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay attention to spec.md FR-11 and design.md §7.4.1 worked example (SourceHints usage pattern).</step>
    <step order="2">Sketch `ResourceDetail` response shape: ToolId, DisplayName, FullDescription, ParameterSchema (the full JSON Schema document), SourceHints per parameter, SampleInvocations[], HumanGate config, PhaseRestrictions, EvidenceRequired, Classification, CostClass, LatencyClass. Document defaults for missing fields.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `GetResourceDetailTool.cs`: `[KernelFunction, Description("Get full schema and parameter source hints for a Tool Registry entry by ID. Use after FindResources to plan invocation.")]` `Task&lt;ResourceDetail&gt; GetResourceDetailAsync(string resourceId)`. Inject Dataverse client + ICallerContext.</step>
    <step order="4">Read the `sprk_toolregistry` record via Dataverse client by `resourceId`. Handle not-found: return a `ResourceDetail` with `ErrorKind=NotFound` (or throw `ResourceNotFoundException` if BFF convention is to propagate). Document the choice in code comments.</step>
    <step order="5">Authorization check: verify caller has permission to inspect this Tool (read permission is broader than invoke permission — design choice: caller MUST hold at least the Tool's read permission). If forbidden, return error or throw.</step>
    <step order="6">Project the Dataverse record into `ResourceDetail` — preserving the parameter schema as a `JsonElement` or string (LLM consumes structurally). Inflate `SourceHints` per parameter from the stored parameter-schema document.</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit tests: (a) happy path returns detail with all metadata + parameter schema + SourceHints, (b) not-found returns ProblemDetails-equivalent error, (c) caller without read permission returns forbidden error, (d) parameter schema round-trips intact, (e) SourceHints distinguish auto-resolvable from user-required correctly.</step>
    <step order="8">Verify build + tests + format: `dotnet build`, `dotnet test --filter "GetResourceDetail"`, `dotnet format`.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify NFR-10 (no new packages). Confirm no publish-size delta.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on `GetResourceDetailTool.cs`; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (caller auth check inside meta-tool), ADR-010 (DI), ADR-013 (NOT exposed via PublicContracts), ADR-015 (audit auto-applies), ADR-019 (errors propagate cleanly), ADR-029 (no new packages).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 023 ✅. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
    <step order="11">Document deviations in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

